National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice has released a statement praising Tony Blinken, who has been nominated for the position of Deputy Secretary of State. Rice highlights Blinken's two decades of government service and his ability to build consensus on challenging policy issues. She describes him as a tremendous colleague and friend with experience, a calm demeanor, an inclusive approach, keen intellect, and excellent judgment. Rice expresses confidence that if Blinken is confirmed by the Senate, he will bring his talents to the State Department, represent the United States abroad, and shape foreign policy to address current challenges and opportunities.